OL,5, A book that claimed to have solved the 
OL,6, question of who betrayed Anne Frank has
OL,7, been recalled by its Dutch publisher   
OL,8, after its findings were discredited.   
OL,10,FThe book's investigating team suggested
OL,11,Fa Jewish man called Arnold van den     
OL,12,FBergh was responsible for her and her  
OL,13,Ffamily's arrests during World War Two. 
OL,15,FBut since it was published in January, 
OL,16,Fthe work has been widely criticised.   
OL,18,FNow a new report by a team of World War
OL,19,FTwo experts and historians has said its
OL,20,Fresearch does not stand up to scrutiny.
